{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/rbd_guided", "parent": "rbd"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simple Guided RBDs"], "extent": [38, 61]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Configures SOP-based bullet RBD fractured objects from geometry, collider, and guide geometry."], "extent": [61, 164]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [164, 179], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool lets you pick a piece of geometry and configure it as a fractured material simulated with Bullet RBD.  Rather than building a DOP network, it uses the SOP-level tools to build a simple network to work with the RBDs.\nWhen multiple names are found on the selected geometry, an additional ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdconstraintsfromrules", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Constraints From Rules"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdconstraintsfromrules"}, " node will be created to constrain the pieces together prior to fracturing. A ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdconstraintproperties", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Constraint Properties SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdconstraintproperties"}, " will also be added to the chain to allow configuring these connector constraints. "], "extent": [179, 764]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Simple Guided RBDs"], "extent": [764, 807], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object to fracture."], "extent": [807, 859]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/rbd_guided", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/rbd_guided"}, {"type": "ui", "text": ["Simple Guided"]}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Simple FX"]}, " tab."], "extent": [859, 948]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object to use as a collider, if any. This should be a polygonal object or packed geometry. For better performance with animated colliders it is recommended to pack the geometry before applying animated transforms as this will allow you to use the animated attribute on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdconfigure", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Configure SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdconfigure"}, "."], "extent": [948, 1291]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object to act as a guide for the bullet simulation. This should be either a polygonal object which can be split into multiple pieces from connectivity, or packed geometry. "], "extent": [1291, 1495]}], "container": true}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdmaterialfracture", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Material Fracture"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdmaterialfracture"}, " and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdbulletsolver", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Bullet Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdbulletsolver"}, " help."], "extent": [1495, 1648]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Working with Simple Guided RBDs"], "extent": [1648, 1686], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can change the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Material Type"]}, " and on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdmaterialfracture", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Material Fracture "], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdmaterialfracture"}, " node. The default material is ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Concrete"]}, ", but you can choose either ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Glass"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Wood"]}, ", or to create ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Custom"]}, " cutting planes."], "extent": [1686, 1923], "body": [{"type": "col_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1923, 1934], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/destruction/concrete", "type": "link", "text": ["Working with concrete"], "fullpath": "/destruction/concrete"}, " for more information.\n        ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/destruction/simple_concrete.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1934, 2079]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/destruction/wood", "type": "link", "text": ["Working with wood"], "fullpath": "/destruction/wood"}, " for more information.\n        ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/destruction/simple_wood.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2079, 2217]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [2217, 2227], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/destruction/glass", "type": "link", "text": ["Working with glass"], "fullpath": "/destruction/glass"}, " for more information.\n        ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/destruction/simple_glass.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2227, 2363]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/destruction/custom", "type": "link", "text": ["Using custom cutters"], "fullpath": "/destruction/custom"}, " for more information.\n        ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/destruction/custom.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2363, 2493]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rbdconfigure", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Configure SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rbdconfigure"}, " allows you to modify the various bullet specific attributes to drive the simulation for both the fractured geometry as well as the collision geometry."], "extent": [2493, 2693]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The guide geometry needs to be broken into various pieces for the guiding to work best. Each piece will be used as a guide piece (or cluster) with its own transform matrix to guide the bullet pieces with. A single deforming piece of geometry will therefore need to be broken into various parts for the deformation to carry across to the RBD simulation."], "extent": [2693, 3049]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["For more information, see ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/destruction/guidedsims", "type": "link", "text": ["Guided simulations"], "fullpath": "/destruction/guidedsims"}, "."], "extent": [3049, 3124]}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["Simple Guided RBDs"], "summary": ["Configures SOP-based bullet RBD fractured objects from geometry, collider, and guide geometry."]}